close_reason: "Superseded by ops-f4vp / PR #6 (feat/agent-enhancement-pass). #6 already adds the schema capability (verified: all 7 commands activate, failed_count 0), so #5's manifest-schema fix is redundant. #5's manifest_version:2/permissions extras are not needed (#6 handles subprocess/EALLOWSCRIPTS at code level). PR #5 closed as superseded by #6."
body: "pm-ops failed to activate after install: registerCommand flags requires the 'schema' capability in the manifest. Added 'schema' to capabilities plus manifest_version + permissions (fs_read/fs_write/subprocess). Verified all 4 commands (scan/policy/verify-release/report) now activate and run correctly against real repos. This was blocking the first npm release."
